                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12571722" author="narayanan" created="Sat, 23 Feb 2008 11:29:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As part of the comments in Derby-3428 the following was said by Jorgen -&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am a little concerned that StandardException has to be introduced to the o.a.d.database.Database interface. I read the comments in that file a couple of times, and it seems that this interface is for methods that are external, like system procedures. I think o.a.d.iapi.db.Database would be more fitting since failover can only be called intarnally (hence i(nternal)api). This does not only apply to the failover method, but to all the replication methods. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12571877" author="narayanan" created="Sun, 24 Feb 2008 08:44:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch moves the replication methods from &lt;br/&gt;
org.apache.derby.database.Database to org.apache.derby.iapi.db.Database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The methods could all be converted to throw StandardException&lt;br/&gt;
instead of SQLException. But this introduces changes to a number of&lt;br/&gt;
other files also which I feel can be done at a later stage probably as&lt;br/&gt;
a follow-up to this issue or as a seperate issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran the basic replication steps, startslave, startmaster, failover and it&lt;br/&gt;
worked fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I request for this patch to be please considered for a commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572093" author="oysteing" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2008 14:43:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. Can you regenerate the patch since the last commit on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3205&quot; title=&quot;Replication: Add connection url command options for starting, stopping slave and for failover&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-3205&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-3205&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a method that should also be moved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572175" author="narayanan" created="Mon, 25 Feb 2008 19:22:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Includes the method isInSlaveMode() among the moved methods. I modified the javadoc&lt;br/&gt;
of isInSlaveMode() to what I think is right.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Nit Picking: The javadoc for the isInSlaveMode() was not right. The description&lt;br/&gt;
                   part of the javadoc should mention what the method is used for and &lt;br/&gt;
                   the @return tag should mention what the return values are.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;                   I generally find the following page useful when I am doubtful about how&lt;br/&gt;
                   to write javadoc&lt;br/&gt;
                   &lt;a href=&quot;http://java.sun.com/j2se/javadoc/writingdoccomments/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://java.sun.com/j2se/javadoc/writingdoccomments/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572846" author="oysteing" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2008 09:43:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed patch, Derby3455_v2.diff, as revision 631527.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hope there will be a follow-up patch that unwraps the SQLExcpetions into&lt;br/&gt;
StandardException for these methods.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12572850" author="narayanan" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2008 09:54:52 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the review and commit Oystein.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I will submit a follow-up patch for this issue!&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12586296" author="narayanan" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2008 09:25:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have raised Derby-3600 to address the follow-up mentioned here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
